To eliminate the direct influence of sampling day and viral load (which differ significantly between those subsets; 

  Fig 2A
 ), analysis was restricted to samples collected on day 4 post onset of symptoms. Ct values were similar for the DENV IgG IIFT negative and positive samples in this subgroup (p = 0.2892), nevertheless, all 9 DENV IgG IIFT negative samples were tested positive in the SD Bioline Dengue Duo NS1 rapid test (

  Fig 2B
 ) while only 50% (13/26) of DENV IgG IIFT positive samples generated a positive result in this test (

  Fig 2C
 ). Although this observation is of borderline statistical significance (p = 0.0131) due to the small sample numbers, it may indicate a direct influence of DENV-specific IgG antibodies on NS1 antigen test sensitivity.
